# File Size Discipline

No file exceeds its size budget without a named exception.

## Thresholds

| File type | Hard limit | Soft warning |
|---|---|---|
| Code | 300 lines | 250 |
| Tests | 400 lines | 300 |
| Docs | 500 lines | 300 |
| Work orders | 600 lines | 450 |

## Exemptions

Always exempt:
- lockfiles
- fixtures and seed data
- migrations
- vendored code
- generated files marked `GENERATED` or `DO NOT EDIT`
- audit artifacts under `docs/audits/`

## Exception Marker

When a file truly cannot be split:

```text
FILE-SIZE-EXCEPTION: ADR-XXXX or WO-XXXX — one-line reason
```

Put the marker in the first 10 lines of the file and reference a real ADR or WO.

## Enforcement

Mechanical gate:

```bash
bash scripts/validate-file-size.sh
```

## Rule

- Split files before they become hard breaches
- Prefer decomposition over exception markers
- Never use the marker as a shortcut for unfinished refactoring
